channel.title: What do you guys do when you feel uninspired
channel.description: Guys for like a month ive been trying to make music but when i make some progress i just feel like im just redoing my old songs.What do you guys do when you feel like that you just keep repeating the same thing?

item.title: What do you guys do when you feel uninspired
item.dc:creator: akabillposters
item.description:
Pinewoodog:

use Ableton’s Audio to Midi feature then copy the midi to Auxy

Apple’s own Music Memos app has a similar feature, although rather than creating midi notes, if tells you the actual notes.
It’s a good step towards understanding the music you’re making.

item.title: What do you guys do when you feel uninspired
item.dc:creator: xavior
item.description:
When I get a creative block, I like to go back to my very old projects that I know I’m never going to release and I fiddle with them. Playing around, experimenting, and ultimately f*cking stuff up gets the juices flowing and really sparks new inspirations. Tearing things apart gives you new tools to build back up again.

Read full topic

item.title: What do you guys do when you feel uninspired
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
Ya, and making music isn’t really easy, even when you’re using something as slick and user friendly as Auxy. Sometimes it’s down right agonizing lol. I’ll def agree the more you work around Auxy (or any tool) it will become more second nature and you’ll know how to achieve whatever sound is in your head in your toolset (at least a little easier, still not a cake walk lol)
